      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Pentalene is a most elusive molecule that has been isolated only at liquid-nitrogen temperature. The pentalene dianion, however, is well known and quite stable. Explain.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBanNWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--1c1c7ca4458b14a3b76340a458be6e4f11e29d38/OChem_15_EC_014.jpg\" alt=\"Pentalene has two fused cyclopentadiene rings. Pentalene dianion structure is similar to pentalene, except that pentalene dianion is enclosed in square brackets with 2 minus charge.\">",
